args: It's a power that's only possible through\na mutually agreed pact with a dragon.
I admit it seems fundamentally different\nto that of the seeds I search for.
Then you accept His Highness's\ninnocence in this matter?
Yes. My apologies for doubting you.
Come to think of it, you haven't told us\nabout these seeds beyond the name.
Maybe you can fill us in?
The seeds of the abyss are terrifying\nfiends that absorb humans, increasing\nsignificantly in size as they do.
At first, they look like a small fleshy lump,\nbut as they ensnare humans in their\ntentacles, they become massive.
And you know this for true?
I cannot doubt what I have seen\nwith my own eyes.
For I saw one of the fell beasts absorb\nmany people in Levin.
Yes. And though the knights banded\ntogether to stop it...it was too late.
Large portions of the kingdom had been\ndestroyed, and countless citizens perished.
But why do you still search for the fiend\nif you have already defeated it?
Because there is yet another seed.
We kept it under the tightest of guard,\nbut it was stolen nevertheless.
Now I understand why you've come\nso far in search of it.
I can see why people call you a champion.\nYou certainly have the spirit of one.
I do not deserve that title.
That's not true at all. You'reâ€”
Enough. I am tired and must rest.
Aw, man! Look how sad he looks as he\nwalks away! His little shoulders are all\nslumped over and everything.
As I find myself unable to relax,\nI came to do some training.
Perhaps we can train together, then.
I'd love to see how I fare against\nthe famous Thunderswift Lord.
Oh man, awesome! Fight, fight, fight!\nEr, but I'm gonna watch from over here.
Impressive. I did not expect you would\nbe able to withstand that blow.
Withstanding it was the best I could do.\nI see now how you got your name.
Your skills are impressive as well.\nI'd love to recruit you as a knight.
Well, you BOTH looked great from here.\nThat was some seriously intense training!
I think we ought to stop for today.
I want to go back to what we were talking\nabout this afternoon. Is there something\nyou're still keeping from us?
If something is worrying you,\nyou can share it with us.
I'm not trying to be kind as such.
But now that we've met, if there's anything\nI can do to help you, I'd be happy to.
In that case, I shall reveal all.
The one responsible for first bringing the\nseeds of the abyss into Levin was my\nfatherâ€”head of the knights at the time.
He was tempted by their immense mana,\nand wanted their power for his own gain.
Wait. Your DAD did all this?!
In the end, one of the seeds absorbed\nhim and turned him into a fiend.
It was my slaying him that led to me\nbeing called Levin's Champion.
Yet I am no hero. Not at all.\nMy hands are stained with blood.
And that sense of guilt is what drove\nyou to try and find the missing seed...
Honestly, this just makes me\nrespect you all the more.
I've been fighting for a long time, but it's\nonly because I've had friends at my side.
But you've been fighting in a\nstrange land all alone.
That's a feat worthy of respect.
Anyway, what do you say to us\nhelping you find the last seed?
A burden shared is a burden halved,\nafter all.
I appreciate the sentiment,\nbut why go so far for me?
Because you're in need of help.\nIs there any better reason?
That's why you helped us, right?
Heh. I suppose this is true.
Great! It's settled! Now let's all get\nsome sleep already, yeah?
If we stay up much later, Cleo's gonna\nhave some choice words for us.
